<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-10T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-10T01:00:00-05:00" n="733" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d733">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/11064: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-10T14:00:00+08:00">November 10, 1937—2
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 7:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>902. My 885 [<hi rend="italic">890</hi>], November 5, 11 a.m.
                                Representative of American Aviation Company states Chinese
                                Government has asked for and <pb facs="0679" n="672" xml:id="pg_672"/> is accepting tenders for pursuit and training planes costing
                                approximately $3,000,000, $2,000,000, respectively and spare parts
                                and engines $1,000,000 each American currency. I understand tenders
                                submitted provide for cash payment and delivery ex-warehouse in the
                                United States. These purchases if made will indicate that the
                                Chinese Army has intention of resisting indefinitely.</p>
                            <p>Sent to the Department, Peiping, Tokyo.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>